Contaminated beer served at a funeral has killed 56 people in Mozambique.

Another 49 people were admitted to hospital and 149 treated for the poisoning in the Chitima and Songo districts in the northeastern Tete province.

The guests taken ill had drunk Pombe, a traditional Mozambican beer, made from millet or corn flour.

